.TH ksct 1 "Jun 2024" "2.3" "User Manual"
.SH NAME
ksct \- X11 set screen color temperature
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B xsct 
[options] 
.I [temperature]
.I [brightness]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B ksct
sets the screen's color temperature.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B -h, --help
Display usage information and exit
.TP
.B -v, --verbose
Display debugging information
.TP
.B -d, --delta
Shift temperature and brightness by temperature and brightness value
.TP
.B -s, --screen N
Zero-based index of screen to use.
.TP
.B -t, --toggle
Toggle between night and day temperature.
.TP
.B -c, --crtc N
Zero-based index of CRTC to use.
.TP
.I [temperature]
Black body temperature
.br
If the value is 0, ksct sets the color temperature to the default of 6500
.br
If no arguments are passed, ksct estimates the current display temperature and brightness
.TP
.I [brightness]
Linear brightness between 0.0 (inclusive) and 1.0 (inclusive). The default value is 1.0 if no parameter is passed.

.SH EXIT STATUS
ksct exits with an exit status of 0 on success and a non-zero value 0 on failure.

.SH AUTHOR
ksct is based on sct by Ted Unangst <tedu@openbsd.org>

.SH SEE ALSO
redshift(1), xtemp(1)
